post_text: The Vigo PTO proudly announces Christopher Gartner as the 2020 Vigo School Outstanding Alumni. This scholarship is presented by the Vigo PTO to a former Bulldog who excelled academically and participated in extra-curricular and community activities throughout high school. Chris was a member of the LHS Marching Band, Concert, Jazz, and Pep Bands, VIP Drumline, and Stage Crew for the LHS musicals. He maintained a 3.9 GPA while successfully completing his general studies coursework at Vincennes University. His future plans include continuing his education at V.U. then transferring to Purdue University to pursue a degree in Civil Engineering. Chris is the son of Teresa and Tim Gartner. Congratulations to Chris and all of our 2020 graduates!

VCSC News
April 9 at 1:56 PM ¬∑

Good morning all,

I certainly know that many of you are dealing with larger issues this morning from the storm. It is an E-Learning or counted day for education in the VCSC but this is secondary and quite frankly if it does not occur today, it does not occur.

Many of you are without power and this includes many of our staff members as well and they simply may not be available during the hours of 9AM to 2PM.

As we have learned with Covid-19, we have to be flexible. We just did not know that today that Covid-19 would become secondary for many of us and our attention would turn elsewhere and with this we must be flexible today and patient as we have too many people dealing with much larger issues than that of education and this is primarily related to the storm from last night.

Hopefully we will slowly start to return to what is the new normal for the time being, but today, education is far more secondary.

Hope you all are safe and with this, please stay safe!

Mr. Parsley

post_text: Monday, March 30th is a big day at Vigo! From 9 AM to 12 PM, new learning packets will be available for pick up. EVERY student has a NEW packet that takes us to our new school closure date of May 1. If your student did not receive the original packet it will be waiting for pick up also. Enter on Vigo Street, drive toward the playground and come through the bus lane and approach door 4. Roll down your car window and our teachers will be there to distribute packets. Food distribution will be ongoing 9-11 AM just like last like last week at door 6. Teachers will also be back out on the bus lane at 5-6 PM for those who cannot make it by in the morning. Please note food distribution is AM only. Be watching the videos posted here to access your child‚Äôs Google Classroom and stayed tuned for more important information in the days ahead as eLearning gets underway. We look forward to seeing everyone at Vigo on Monday.

If you have additional questions and/or concerns, please feel free to contact us anytime on our VCSC Helpline. (vcschelp@vcsc.k12.in.us or 812-882-6376)

VCSC News
March 9 at 5:40 PM ¬∑

VCSC Kindergarten Registration is HERE, with an early online option!

On Tuesday, March 10th from 4pm-6:30pm all VCSC elementary schools will be hosting kindergarten registration.

To register your child, please go to the school district that your child lives in. Yes, you will still need to go to the school on registration day EVEN IF YOU FILL OUT THE INFORMATION ONLINE.

To find what district you live in, please click on the link and enter your address.

Find my district: https://sites.google.com/vcsc.k12.in.us/vcsc-elementary-school-distric/home?fbclid=IwAR1vxmvX0_U75chcMjES5ho_Qxtymd0prqP3XL4ywdVCj9l7UeFmd5YcmRc

Please bring your child‚Äôs birth certificate, immunization records, and proof of address.

Your child must be 5 years old by August 1, 2020.

Online Kindergarten Registration: https://sites.google.com/vcsc.k12.in.us/vcsc-kg-reg-2033/home

We can‚Äôt wait to see you!
